CASCADE VERSION-BOOKKEEPING VALIDATED + SIBLING-PULL HYGIENE (2026-06-15): the cascade's version bump-back works correctly - CI bumps rs-plugkit Cargo.toml patch, builds+publishes plugkit.wasm, and commits the bumped Cargo.toml back to rs-plugkit main (e.g. commit 3f3ccc5 -> 0.1.645), so the Cargo.toml source-of-truth tracks the published wasm with no drift. Validated this fire: rs-plugkit Cargo (origin) = npm plugkit-wasm = gm.json plugkitVersion = running+installed wasm = 0.1.645; gm-plugkit npm 2.0.1556. HYGIENE LESSON: a local rs-* checkout goes STALE after CI's bump-back commit (my local was 1 behind at 261c686/0.1.644 while origin was 3f3ccc5/0.1.645). Before working in or pushing a sibling rs-* repo, git fetch + ff-merge origin/main first; pushing from a stale local would attempt to revert the CI version bump (git_push rebase-retry would catch it, but pull-first is cleaner and avoids the churn).